\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {16}{\ignorespaces Robustness of cross-backbone reversal to entropy quantile-normalization. For each (env, backbone) cell, we report Spearman $\rho (\sigma , U)$ (mathematically invariant under within-cell monotone transforms of $\sigma $, so shared across raw/S1/S2/S3) and Pearson $\rho $ under raw vs.\ three quantile-normalization schemes: \textbf  {S1} (per-(env, backbone)) ranks within each cell; \textbf  {S2} (per-backbone) ranks within each backbone's pool; \textbf  {S3} (per-environment) ranks within each environment's pool. We list the \textbf  {11 strong-signal cells} (raw Pearson $|\rho |\geq 0.13$)—every cell the paper's reversal claim invokes, including the cross-backbone anchors on HotpotQA, APPS, and FEVER. \textbf  {Robust} = sign stable vs.\ raw under all three schemes (CI excludes 0 on the same side). $^{\ddagger }$ Phi-3.5 APPS is robust under S1, S2 but inconclusive under S3 ($-0.054$, CI straddles zero). For completeness, 4 weak- signal cells (raw $|\rho |<0.13$, CIs already straddle zero in raw data; paper does not claim reversal there) and 3 cells with insufficient logged data are discussed in the surrounding prose and not reproduced here. $^*$: $p<0.05$. 1000-resample bootstrap.\relax }}{25}{table.caption.48}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:phase-a-norm}{{16}{25}{Robustness of cross-backbone reversal to entropy quantile-normalization. For each (env, backbone) cell, we report Spearman $\rho (\sigma , U)$ (mathematically invariant under within-cell monotone transforms of $\sigma $, so shared across raw/S1/S2/S3) and Pearson $\rho $ under raw vs.\ three quantile-normalization schemes: \textbf {S1} (per-(env, backbone)) ranks within each cell; \textbf {S2} (per-backbone) ranks within each backbone's pool; \textbf {S3} (per-environment) ranks within each environment's pool. We list the \textbf {11 strong-signal cells} (raw Pearson $|\rho |\geq 0.13$)—every cell the paper's reversal claim invokes, including the cross-backbone anchors on HotpotQA, APPS, and FEVER. \textbf {Robust} = sign stable vs.\ raw under all three schemes (CI excludes 0 on the same side). $^{\ddagger }$ Phi-3.5 APPS is robust under S1, S2 but inconclusive under S3 ($-0.054$, CI straddles zero). For completeness, 4 weak- signal cells (raw $|\rho |<0.13$, CIs already straddle zero in raw data; paper does not claim reversal there) and 3 cells with insufficient logged data are discussed in the surrounding prose and not reproduced here. $^*$: $p<0.05$. 1000-resample bootstrap.\relax }{table.caption.48}{}}
